<p>GDP growth: 3.8% GDP: $30bn (PPP: $37bn) Inflation: 6.0% Population: 6.7m GDP per head: $4,500 (PPP: $5,630)</p>

<p>Since buying off dissenters as the Arab spring bloomed elsewhere, King Abdullah II has walked a narrow line between angry protesters and cosseted vested interests. Protests will continue but, backed by a loyal and efficient army, the king will manage to stay on the throne. The purchase of peace was not cheap; the budget gap will stay high, but foreign grants to the pro-Western regime will fill it comfortably.</p>

